                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-162-off973 t18310217-162-crimeloc976"></join>. The prisoner has lodged there three months; he had the back room on the first floor; a man his wife, and a little boy, live in the back parlour - the property stated was taken from the table drawer in the back parlour; the prisoner had no right there - I missed it on the 17th of January, but the prisoner had left on the 11th of January - I missed several other articles; I first missed the gown, and in seeking for that I discovered the property which he had pawned two months before; he came to me as a single man - he is a shoemaker, and might have plenty of work.</p>
