            . I am shopman to Mr. Brickhill, a pawnbroker, in Tottenham-court-road. I have a shift and towel, pawned by the prisoner on the 15th of November; they are both claimed by the prosecutrix.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I left there, and went to No. 5, Little Camden-street; the prosecutrix came and said they wanted to see my room; I let them in, and they took me - I owed them a trifle of money, and I pawned the articles for leather to make some shoes - her son used to sleep in the same room when he was at home.</p>
               <p>
            
